I'm partial to keeping a "bind" function handy. (Function#bind will be in ECMAScript 5, but it's not quite here yet). It's crucial for keeping your sanity when trying to use "this" with callbacks, Ajax, or async.<p><pre><code>    var bind = function(func, context) {
      var slice = Array.prototype.slice;
      var args  = slice.call(args, 2);
      return function() {
        return func.apply(context || {}, args.concat(slice.call(arguments)));
      };
    };</code></pre>
